<HEADLINE>
FT  04 MAY 93 / Cambodian guerrillas attack town
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
UP TO 500 Khmer Rouge guerrillas attacked the strategic town of Siem Reap in
northern Cambodia yesterday, pushing civilians ahead of them as human
shields, according to United Nations peacekeepers, Reuter reports.
It was the biggest attack on a town since Cambodia's four warring factions
signed a UN-sponsored peace pact in 1991 that the Khmer Rouge has since
abandoned. The guerrillas attacked before dawn but one UN military observer
said the assault was disorganised.
The Khmer Rouge has threatened to use violence to disrupt elections
scheduled for May 23-27.
