<HEADLINE>
FT  04 MAY 93 / Khmer Rouge attacks town
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PHNOM PENH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
KHMER ROUGE guerrillas firing automatic rifles and rocket-propelled grenades
attacked a provincial capital in northwest Cambodia yesterday, AP reports
from Phnom Penh.
Guerrillas were firing on the airport runway at Siem Reap, said UN
officials. The Kampuchea Airlines commercial flight which many foreign
tourists take from Phnom Penh to visit the famed temples of Angkor just
outside Siem Reap was cancelled.
UN military observers in Siem Reap, 225 km northwest of Phnom Penh, had long
been preparing for an attack, building bunkers and installing razor wire
around their compounds.
A UN interpreter said the Khmer Rouge attacked at 5 a m and fighting was
continuing at 9 a m. The Bangladeshi infantry battalion, which is posted
there to protect UN workers, did not answer their phone. The Khmer Rouge has
boycotted the UN operation to guide the country through democratic elections
this month.
