FT  01 MAY 93 / Food &amp; Drink: Food Markets
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
FOOD markets are wonderful, exciting and evocative. The colours they
generate, their scents and smells and bustle all paint a picture of how, not
so long ago, we all used to shop.
If you go with an open mind as to what to buy, markets can be inspirational
and vividly demonstrate just how the year is evolving - from the first
bundles of English asparagus to the first summer fruits (in France, the
first cherry crop is still despatched from Ceret in the Pyrenees to the
Elysee Palace) to the melon market of Cavaillon, to wild mushrooms and the
onset of autumn and the truffle markets of Piedmont.
Over the next few months Weekend FT food and drink writers will be visiting
some eye-catching markets, starting this week with Giles MacDonogh in Venice
. . .
