<HEADLINE>
FT  01 MAY 93 / Treaty view challenged
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALISON SMITH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE STAKES were raised in the parliamentary battle over the Maastricht bill
yesterday with the publication of the legal opinion obtained by Tory
Euro-sceptics about the amendment on the social chapter.
The opinion challenges the government's view that passing the amendment
would not affect the UK's ability to ratify the treaty. Almost 300 MPs have
put their names to the amendment, which would exclude from the bill the
protocol containing the social chapter and the UK's 'opt-out'.
Miss Betty Boothroyd, the Speaker of the Commons, will consider over the
weekend which amendments to the legislation should be chosen for debate and
vote on Tuesday and Wednesday of next week when MPs resume their detailed
discussion of the bill. She will announce her decisions on Tuesday.
