<TEXT>
MR Chris Patten, Hong Kong's governor, left yesterday for a one-week trip to
the US, where he will meet President Bill Clinton and press for
unconditional renewal of China's most favoured nation status, writes Simon
Holberton in Hong Kong.
Mr Patten will also meet senior administration officials and congressional
